e\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Plan: Support Cursor CLI Hook Differences\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe Cursor agent implementation was built from Cursor IDE hook samples. We now have real hook data from **Cursor CLI** and need to update the implementation to support both. The critical issue is that Cursor CLI never provides `transcript_path`, which breaks the turn-end handler.\\n\\n**Source data**: IDE log (`simple-session-ide.log`), CLI log (`simple-session-agent-cli.log`), CLI transcript (`agent-transcripts/723fa68d-....jsonl`)\\n\\n## Corrected Differences (IDE vs CLI)\\n\\nComparing both logs reveals the actual differences:\\n\\n| Hook | IDE `transcript_path` | CLI `transcript_path` |\\n|------|----------------------|----------------------|\\n| sessionStart | `null` | `null` |\\n| beforeSubmitPrompt | `null` | `null` |\\n| **stop** | **nested path provided** | **`null`** |\\n| **sessionEnd** | **nested path provided** | **`null`** |\\n\\n| Aspect | Cursor IDE | Cursor CLI |\\n|--------|-----------|------------|\\n| Transcript location | `agent-transcripts/<id>/<id>.jsonl` (nested dir) | `agent-transcripts/<id>.jsonl` (flat file) |\\n| `transcript_path` on stop/sessionEnd | Provided | `null` |\\n| `cursor_version` format | Semver (`2.5.17`) | Date-based (`2026.02.13-41ac335`) |\\n| `composer_mode` on sessionStart | Present (`\\\"agent\\\"`) | Absent |\\n| `model` on sessionStart | `\\\"default\\\"` | Actual model name |\\n| `sessionEnd` richer fields | Present (both have `reason`, `duration_ms`, etc.) | Present |\\n| `stop` extra fields | Present (both have `status`, `loop_count`) | Present |\\n\\n**Key insight**: `sessionEnd` richer fields (`reason`, `duration_ms`, `is_background_agent`, `final_status`) and `stop` extra fields (`status`, `loop_count`) exist in **both** IDE and CLI — they were always there, just not captured by our types.\\n\\n## Critical Issue\\n\\nCLI `stop` hook has `transcript_path: null`, so `SessionRef` is empty on TurnEnd. The lifecycle dispatcher (`lifecycle.go:161-163`) errors:\\n```go\\nif transcriptRef == \\\"\\\" {\\n    return errors.New(\\\"transcript file not specified\\\")\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Fix `GetSessionDir` to include `agent-transcripts/`\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor.go:78-89`\\n\\nCurrent: `~/.cursor/projects/<sanitized-path>`\\nFix: `~/.cursor/projects/<sanitized-path>/agent-transcripts`\\n\\nThis matches the real filesystem layout in both IDE and CLI.\\n\\n### 2. Fix `ResolveSessionFile` to support both flat (CLI) and nested (IDE) layouts\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor.go:70-72`\\n\\nCurrent: `<sessionDir>/<id>.jsonl`\\nFix: Check both:\\n1. `<sessionDir>/<id>/<id>.jsonl` (IDE nested) — if exists, return it\\n2. `<sessionDir>/<id>.jsonl` (CLI flat) — fallback/default\\n\\nSame pattern as `geminicli.ResolveSessionFile`.\\n\\n### 3. Compute transcript path in `ParseHookEvent` when `transcript_path` is null\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/lifecycle.go`\\n\\nOnly needed for `stop` (TurnEnd) and `sessionEnd` — those are the hooks where IDE provides the path but CLI doesn't. For sessionStart and beforeSubmitPrompt, `transcript_path` is null in **both** IDE and CLI, and the system already handles that.\\n\\nWhen `raw.TranscriptPath` is empty on stop/sessionEnd:\\n- Use `paths.WorktreeRoot(ctx)` to get repo root (same approach as OpenCode)\\n- Call `c.GetSessionDir(repoRoot)` then `c.ResolveSessionFile(sessionDir, conversationID)`\\n- Change `_ context.Context` to `ctx context.Context` in parse methods that need it\\n\\nExtract a helper like `(c *CursorAgent) resolveTranscriptRef(ctx, sessionID, rawPath) string` to keep it DRY.\\n\\n### 4. Enrich types to capture fields present in both IDE and CLI\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/types.go`\\n\\n**a) Add `sessionEndRaw` struct** (currently uses generic `sessionInfoRaw`):\\n- `SessionID`, `Reason`, `DurationMs`, `IsBackgroundAgent`, `FinalStatus`\\n- These fields exist in both IDE and CLI\\n\\n**b) Add `stopHookInputRaw` struct** (currently uses generic `sessionInfoRaw`):\\n- `Status`, `LoopCount`\\n- These fields exist in both IDE and CLI\\n\\n**c) Add `sessionStartRaw` struct** (currently uses generic `sessionInfoRaw`):\\n- `SessionID`, `IsBackgroundAgent`, `ComposerMode` (IDE-only)\\n\\nUpdate corresponding parse functions in `lifecycle.go` to use the new types.\\n\\n### 5. Update tests\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/lifecycle_test.go`\\n- Add tests with `transcript_path` absent/null (CLI pattern) for stop and sessionEnd\\n- Add test with real CLI hook payload from `simple-session-agent-cli.log`\\n- Existing tests (with `transcript_path` provided) remain for IDE backward compat\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor_test.go`\\n- `TestCursorAgent_GetSessionDir_DefaultPath`: verify path ends with `agent-transcripts`\\n- `TestCursorAgent_ResolveSessionFile`: test both flat and nested layouts\\n- Add test for `ResolveSessionFile` preferring nested when it exists\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor.go` — `GetSessionDir`, `ResolveSessionFile`\\n2. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/lifecycle.go` — transcript path fallback, use ctx\\n3. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/types.go` — `sessionEndRaw`, `stopHookInputRaw`, `sessionStartRaw`\\n4. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/lifecycle_test.go` — CLI-format tests\\n5. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor_test.go` — updated session dir/file tests\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n2. `go test ./cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/... -v` — cursor-specific tests\\n3. Test with exact JSON from both `simple-session-ide.log` and `simple-session-agent-cli.log`\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/robin/.claude/proj