 DetectPresence, ProtectedDirs\\n    17→//   - Transcript Storage (3 methods): ReadTranscript, ChunkTranscript, ReassembleTranscript\\n    18→//   - Legacy (6 methods): Will be moved to optional interfaces or removed in a future phase\\n    19→type Agent interface {\\n    20→\\t// --- Identity ---\\n    21→\\n    22→\\t// Name returns the agent registry key (e.g., \\\"claude-code\\\", \\\"gemini\\\")\\n    23→\\tName() AgentName\\n    24→\\n    25→\\t// Type returns the agent type identifier (e.g., \\\"Claude Code\\\", \\\"Gemini CLI\\\")\\n    26→\\t// This is stored in metadata and trailers.\\n    27→\\tType() AgentType\\n    28→\\n    29→\\t// Description returns a human-readable description for UI\\n    30→\\tDescription() string\\n    31→\\n    32→\\t// IsPreview returns whether the agent integration is in preview or stable\\n    33→\\tIsPreview() bool\\n    34→\\n    35→\\t// DetectPresence checks if this agent is configured in the repository\\n    36→\\tDetectPresence(ctx context.Context) (bool, error)\\n    37→\\n    38→\\t// ProtectedDirs returns repo-root-relative directories that should never be\\n    39→\\t// modified or deleted during rewind or other destructive operations.\\n    40→\\t// Examples: [\\\".claude\\\"] for Claude, [\\\".gemini\\\"] for Gemini.\\n    41→\\tProtectedDirs() []string\\n    42→\\n    43→\\t// --- Transcript Storage ---\\n    44→\\n    45→\\t// ReadTranscript reads the raw transcript bytes for a session.\\n    46→\\tReadTranscript(sessionRef string) ([]byte, error)\\n    47→\\n    48→\\t// ChunkTranscript splits a transcript into chunks if it exceeds maxSize.\\n    49→\\t// Returns a slice of chunks. If the transcript fits in one chunk, returns single-element slice.\\n    50→\\t// The chunking is format-aware: JSONL splits at line boundaries, JSON splits message arrays.\\n    51→\\tChunkTranscript(ctx context.Context, content []byte, maxSize int) ([][]byte, error)\\n    52→\\n    53→\\t// ReassembleTranscript combines chunks back into a single transcript.\\n    54→\\t// Handles format-specific reassembly (JSONL concatenation, JSON message merging).\\n    55→\\tReassembleTranscript(chunks [][]byte) ([]byte, error)\\n    56→\\n    57→\\t// --- Legacy methods (will move to optional interfaces in Phase 4) ---\\n    58→\\n    59→\\t// GetSessionID extracts session ID from hook input.\\n    60→\\tGetSessionID(input *HookInput) string\\n    61→\\n    62→\\t// GetSessionDir returns where agent stores session data for this repo.\\n    63→\\tGetSessionDir(repoPath string) (string, error)\\n    64→\\n    65→\\t// ResolveSessionFile returns the path to the session transcript file.\\n    66→\\tResolveSessionFile(sessionDir, agentSessionID string) string\\n    67→\\n    68→\\t// ReadSession reads session data from agent's storage.\\n    69→\\tReadSession(input *HookInput) (*AgentSession, error)\\n    70→\\n    71→\\t// WriteSession writes session data for resumption.\\n    72→\\tWriteSession(ctx context.Context, session *AgentSession) error\\n    73→\\n    74→\\t// FormatResumeCommand returns command to resume a session.\\n    75→\\tFormatResumeCommand(sessionID string) string\\n    76→}\\n    77→\\n    78→// HookSupport is implemented by agents with lifecycle hooks.\\n    79→// This optional interface allows agents like Claude Code and Cursor IDE to\\n    80→// install and manage hooks that notify Entire of agent events.\\n    81→//\\n    82→// The interface is organized into two groups:\\n    83→//   - Hook Mapping (2 methods): HookNames, ParseHookEvent\\n    84→//   - Hook Management (3 methods): InstallHooks, UninstallHooks, AreHooksInstalled\\n    85→type HookSupport interface {\\n    86→\\tAgent\\n    87→\\n    88→\\t// HookNames returns the hook verbs this agent supports.\\n    89→\\t// These become subcommands under `entire hooks <agent>`.\\n    90→\\t// e.g., [\\\"stop\\\", \\\"user-prompt-submit\\\", \\\"session-start\\\", \\\"session-end\\\"]\\n    91→\\tHookNames() []string\\n    92→\\n    93→\\t// ParseHookEvent translates an agent-native hook into a normalized lifecycle Event.\\n    94→\\t// Returns nil if the hook has no lifecycle significance (e.g., pass-through hooks).\\n    95→\\t// This is the core contribution surface for new agent implementations.\\n    96→\\tParseHookEvent(ctx context.Context, hookName string, stdin io.Reader) (*Event, error)\\n    97→\\n    98→\\t// InstallHooks installs agent-specific hooks.\\n    99→\\t// If localDev is true, hooks point to local development build.\\n   100→\\t// If force is true, removes existing Entire hooks before installing.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"b76507a7-46c9-4987-8503-3e372c94dd80\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T12:57:18.942Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"I need to find and read several files. Please:\\n\\n1. Read the Gemini CLI agent's `ResolveSessionFile` method - look in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/` for the file containing it\\n2. Read the OpenCode agent's lifecycle.go to see how it resolves transcript paths when they're missing from hook input - look in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/`\\n3. Read `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/constants.go` or similar to find hook name constants\\n4. Read the cursor log files at the repo root: `cursor.jsonl` (the CLI log data)\\n5. Look for any file like `simple-session-agent-cli.log` or `simple-session-ide.log` in the repo\\n\\nReturn the full content of each file found.\",\"agentId\":\"a48c261\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01UrFTwXifRZmbsYWzWXheUL\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_0182Sy9d5WgiSVR9g9EuKoE1\",\"uuid\":\"4b62155c-fee6-431f-a19a-a109da603242\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T12:57:18.949Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"4b62155c-fee6-431f-a19a-a109da603242\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/robin/Developer/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"70ec55fe-1118-45b1-a450-0f6ca770ae91\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"rwr/tests-for-cursor-agent-cli\",\"slug\":\"gleaming-hopping-ripple\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":